Primitive erythroid cells are nucleated and express the embryonic globins Hba-x (=Zeta) and Hbb-bh1

Recent findings support that there is one more state between primitive and definitive erythyocytes: pro-defintive erythrocytes (e.g. this review article PMID: 33783643). Pro-definitive hematopoietic cells develop directly from hematoendothelial cells / blood progenitors and later migrate to the aorta-gonad-mesonephros region and the liver to give rise to definitive hematopoietic cells, which stay until death / go into bone (marrow). (Pro-) Definitive erythrocytes express Hba-a1 /-a2(alpha) and Hbb-y, and later Hbb-b1/-b2. See PMID: 32467144 and PMID: 20201948 for a detailed description on globin expression and switching
